"{\"uid\": \"express.co.uk-showbiz-tv-radio-2173863-bbc-olympics-viewers-switch-off\", \"text\": \"  BBCfans were not happy with the ongoing coverage of this year'sWinter Olympics, currently taking place in Italy, as they were forced to switch off partway through a segment. Viewers of the cross country event were left furious as the feed suddenly cut, 40km into a 50km race. It switched fromiPlayerto live on BBC Two, but some viewers fumed they were not informed of the change.  One fuming viewer tweeted: \\\"Hugest congrats to the @BBCSport @BBCiPlayer who covered 40km of the 50km cross country this morning and then just decided they could not be bothered to show the finish. WTF? It can not be that difficult to start and finish one race/event on an iPlayer channel.  \\\"I was watching on my phone in the car and suddenly it's just not there anymore. I do not want to switch to BBC2 or TNT. That's not the point.\\\"  Read more:'I am going' - Reform's Laila Cunningham storms off air as migrant row explodes  Read more:'I took famous picture of Andrew after arrest and one thing left me speechless'  Someone reached out to defend theBBC, writing in response: \\\"They switched it from iPlayer to BBC 2, as they have been doing all the way through the Olympics.They even say what they are doing!\\\"  But the original poster clapped back: \\\"Not for at least 10 mins they did not. I was between TNT, iPlayer and BBC2 in the car swearing like a native. So annoying.\\\"  Another echoed: \\\"They have done it yet again. Every bloody event near enough. The worst coverage of the Winter Olympics ever.\\\"  Ensure our latest showbiz headlines always appear at the top of your Google Search by making us a Preferred Source.Click here to activateor add us as a Preferred Source in your Google search settings.    \\\"I saw it too, but what's worse is something starts on one channel, then they switch to another channel, then switch back to the channel it was on in the first place!\\\" somebody else moaned.  It comes after commentator John Hunt had to apologise on airafter a mistake filming Team GB athletes Matt Weston and Tabby Stoecker taking gold in the mixed team skeleton relay event last week.  We use your sign-up to provide content in ways you have consented to and to improve our understanding of you. This may include adverts from us and 3rd parties based on our understanding. You can unsubscribe at any time. Read ourPrivacy Policy  The camera was instead focused on Weston's coach rather than the moment he pushed off to sprint across the ice, and missed his start completely. The broadcast wasn't controlled by the Beeb, rather being part of the official Olympics broadcast, but host John told viewers at home: \\\"Oh, what are they doing?  \\\"What are they playing at? That's terrible. That's a great start. Sorry about the pictures but Matt is on his way.\\\"  SEARCH  CONNECT WITH US  TODAY'S PAPER  See today's front and back pages, download the newspaper, order back issues and use the historic Daily Express newspaper archive.  EXPRESS.CO.UK  Daily Express uses notifications to keep you updated\"}"